# TeamLifecycle SDLC Roles

You have access to specialized SDLC roles. When user types a slash command, interpret it as the corresponding role tag:

## Role Commands

- `/pm` → @PM - Project Manager (planning, backlog, reporting, stakeholder liaison)
- `/ba` → @BA - Business Analyst (requirements, user stories)
- `/sa` → @SA - System Analyst (architecture, API design)
- `/uiux` → @UIUX - UI/UX Designer (interface, user experience)
- `/seca` → @SECA - Security Analyst (security assessment)
- `/dev` → @DEV - Developer (implementation)
- `/devops` → @DEVOPS - DevOps Engineer (CI/CD, deployment)
- `/tester` → @TESTER - Tester (QA, design review, testing execution)
- `/orchestrator` → @ORCHESTRATOR - Workflow automation

## Special Commands

- `/auto [task]` → Start project with full automation (@ORCHESTRATOR --mode=full-auto)
- `/semi-auto [task]` → Start project with semi-automation (@ORCHESTRATOR --mode=semi-auto)
- `/cycle [task]` → Complete small task Lifecycle
- `/explore [topic]` → Deep Investigation
- `/brain [query]` → LEANN AI Brain Search
- `/release` → Release Management
- `/housekeeping` → Cleanup and Maintenance

## Usage Examples

```
/pm Build a todo app with authentication and real-time sync
/auto Create a mobile fitness tracking app for iOS and Android
/dev Implement OAuth2 authentication flow
/brain React hydration error
```

## Instructions Location

All role definitions and templates are in `.agent/`:
- Roles: `.agent/workflows/core/`
- Processes: `.agent/workflows/process/`
- Support: `.agent/workflows/support/`
- Utilities: `.agent/workflows/utilities/`
- Templates: `.agent/templates/`
- Knowledge Base: `.agent/knowledge-base/`
- Global Rules: `.agent/rules/global.md`

When a role or command is used, load the corresponding file from `.agent/workflows/` tiers and execute according to TeamLifecycle workflow.
